Regional Seminar on Media,Education Opens 
A regional seminar on media and education at the grassroots in Africa
opened here today with participants drawn from nine african countries
attended the meeting, Radio Cameroon reported today.
The seminar is aimed at examining the role of the media in enhancing
the education of the masses.
Speaking at the opening ceremony, the representative of the United
Nations Educational and Scientific and Cultural Organization in central
and west Africa reiterated UNSCO's committment in helping educate the
people.
The representative said free press, education for all and the right to
scientific and academic investigations are important in the development
process of people.
the five-day seminar has been organized by UNSCO and the International
Consultative Forum on Education for All.
